Let's look at our `some-metric` line from prev file:
```json
{
  "type": "Metric",
  "data": {
    "name": "some-rate",
    "type": "rate",
    "contains": "default",
    "tainted": null,
    "thresholds": [], // <-- ¯\_(ツ)_/¯ 
    "submetrics": null,
    "sub": {
      "name": "",
      "parent": "",
      "suffix": "",
      "tags": null
    }
  },
  "metric": "some-rate"
}
```
So, as you can see, there is no threshold name in the "thresholds" array, as it described in the [spec](https://docs.k6.io/docs/results-output#section-json-output). I can't know that some thresholds was defined. It's really big problem when I need to analyze results, because I don't know were all thresholds passed or not.
